U.K. Banks Say Commission Proposal Could Hurt Funding, Sky Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-04-04T20:41:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/u-k-banks-say-commission-proposal-could-hurt-funding-sky-says.html
Some of the U.K.’s biggest banks
told the government that if the Independent Commission on
Banking’s interim report due to be published on April 11
includes an option of obliging banks to raise more capital to
fund their investment banking activities, the banks’ abilities
to finance themselves may be impaired, Sky News City Editor Mark
Kleinman  reported , citing an unnamed director at a British bank.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 